{{Infobox person | name = Claude-François Baudez | image = ClaudeBaudezWikipedia.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Baudez in 2012 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1932|12|3|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Paris]], [[France]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2013|7|13|1932|12|3|df=yes}} | death_place = | residence = | nationality = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = [[Mayanist]], [[archaeologist]], [[iconologist]] | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | television = | spouse = | children = | awards = | signature = | website = <!-- {{URL|Example.com}} --> | footnotes = }}
'''Claude-François Baudez''' (3 December 1932 – 13 July 2013) was a French [[Mayanist]], [[archaeologist]] and [[iconologist]]. He was honorary director of research at the [[Centre national de la recherche scientifique]], a specialist on the rituals and beliefs of [[Mesoamerica]], particularly of the [[Maya civilisation]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.babelio.com/auteur/Claude-Francois-Baudez/122866 |title=Claude-François Baudez |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=Babelio |publisher= |accessdate=2018-02-05 |language=fr}}</ref>
== Career == In his early years, Claude-François Baudez studied the little-known remains of [[Mesoamerican civilisations]] in [[Costa Rica]] and [[Honduras]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cemca.org.mx/files_biblio/files/12mh_Baudez_esp.pdf |title=Claude-François BAUDEZ |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=Centro de estudios mexicanos y centroamericanos |publisher= |accessdate=2018-02-05 |language=es-MX}}</ref> Since 1971, he has devoted himself mainly to research on the Maya culture. He was co-director of French excavations at the [[Toniná]] archaeological site in Mexico, and led the [[Copán]] exploration and restoration programme, while studying its sculpture.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iesr.ephe.sorbonne.fr/node/25510 |title=BAUDEZ CLAUDE-FRANÇOIS |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website={{ill|Institut européen en sciences des religions|fr}} |publisher= |accessdate=2018-02-05 |language=fr}}</ref>
He is co-author of {{lang|fr|Le monde précolombien : Les Mayas}}, published in the collection “{{lang|fr|L’Univers des Formes}}” at [[Éditions Gallimard]]; and {{lang|fr|Les cités perdues des Mayas}}, a heavily illustrated [[Pocket edition|pocket book]] from the [[Collection (publishing)|collection]] “[[Découvertes Gallimard]]”, which has been translated into twelve languages, including English.
== Research chronicle == * 1957-1960 Costa Rica: Investigations at the Papagayo site in the Valley of Tempisque. * 1964-1965 Honduras: Investigations in the [[Gulf of Fonseca]] region and in the Valley of [[Comayagua]]. * 1967-1969 Honduras: Excavation at the archaeological region [[Los Naranjos, Honduras|Los Naranjos]] (in collaboration with {{ill|Pierre Becquelin|fr}}). * 1971-1973 Mexico: Excavation at the [[Toniná]] site (in collaboration with Pierre Becquelin). * 1977-1980 Honduras: Direction of the [[Copán]] Archaeological Project. * 1981-1984 Honduras: Annual stays in Copán for [[in-situ]] study of its sculptures. * 1989 Mexico: Stay in [[Palenque]] for in-situ studies of its sculptures. * 1990 Costa Rica: Excavations at the [[Diquís]] Delta. * 1994 Mexico: Iconographic studies at [[Balamku]].
== Selected Bibliography == [[File:TulumCatherwood1844.jpg|thumb|Main temple at [[Tulum]], lithograph by [[Frederick Catherwood]], featured on the cover of ''Lost Cities of the Maya''.]] * ''Recherches Archéologiques dans la vallée du Tempisque, Guanacaste, Costa Rica'', Travaux et Mémoires de l’Institut des Hautes Études de l’Amérique Latine, 1967 * ''Amérique Centrale'', collection « Archaeologia Mundi ». Nagel Publishers, 1970 * Co-author with Pierre Becquelin, ''Le monde précolombien : Les Mayas'', collection « L’Univers des Formes » (nº 31). Éditions Gallimard, 1984 * Co-author with Sydney Picasso, ''Les cités perdues des Mayas'', collection « [[Découvertes Gallimard]] » (nº 20), série Archéologie. Éditions Gallimard, 1987 (new edition in 2008)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gallimard.fr/Catalogue/GALLIMARD/Decouvertes-Gallimard/Decouvertes-Gallimard/Archeologie/Les-cites-perdues-des-Mayas |title=''Les cités perdues des Mayas'', collection Découvertes Gallimard (n° 20) |publisher=[[Éditions Gallimard]] |accessdate=2018-02-06 |language=fr}}</ref> ** US edition – ''Lost Cities of the Maya'', “[[Abrams Discoveries]]” series. Harry N. Abrams, 1992 ** UK edition – ''Lost Cities of the Maya'', ‘[[New Horizons (Thames & Hudson)|New Horizons]]’ series. Thames & Hudson, 1992 * ''[[Jean-Frédéric Waldeck]], peintre : le premier explorateur des ruines mayas'', Hazan, 1993 * ''Maya Sculpture of Copán: The Iconography'', University of Oklahoma Press, 1994 * ''Une histoire de la religion des Mayas : Du panthéisme au panthéon'', collection « Bibliothèque Albin Michel de l’histoire ». Éditions Albin Michel, 2002 * ''Una historia de la religión de los antiguos Mayas'', [[UNAM]], 2004
