'''James L. Blount''' (June 4, 1935 – August 22, 2017) was an American newspaper editor and historian.  Blount was editor of the ''[[Hamilton Journal-News]]'', the daily newspaper in [[Hamilton, Ohio]] and wrote extensively on the history of Hamilton and [[Butler County, Ohio]].

==Biography==
Blount was born June 4, 1935, in Hamilton, Ohio, the oldest of the five children of James and Julia (Mignerey) Blount.<ref name="ddnobit">{{cite news |url=http://www.mydaytondailynews.com/news/hamilton-historian-transportation-guru-dies-age/HAEk2rpgGgX9biETaxNqVO/ |first=Mike |last=Rutledge |title=Hamilton historian, transportation guru dies at age 82 |newspaper=[[Dayton Daily News]] |date=August 23, 2017}}</ref> He graduated from Hamilton High School in 1953 and earned a B.S. in Education from the [[University of Cincinnati]], and an M.A. in history from [[Miami University]].<ref name="ddnobit"/> He began his career in journalism at ''[[The Cincinnati Enquirer]].''<ref name="ddnobit"/> He was hired by the ''[[Hamilton Journal-News]]'' in 1963. Blount was editor of the paper from 1971 to 1986.<ref name="jnobit">{{cite news |url=http://www.journal-news.com/news/south-hamilton-crossing-named-after-local-historian-jim-blount/aopdXgYtwCDGYm400NwEsI/ |first=Mike |last=Rutledge |title=South Hamilton Crossing to be named after local historian Jim Blount |newspaper=[[Journal-News]] |date=June 22, 2017}}</ref>  He wrote a weekly column on local history in the ''Journal News'' from 1988 to 2004.<ref name="jnobit"/>

He left the newspaper to become a high school history teacher in 1986.<ref name="ddnobit"/>

Blount was an advocate for road improvements in Butler County.<ref name="ddnobit"/> He served on the board of directors of the [[Butler County Transportation Improvement District]] from 1994 until his death.<ref name="ddnobit"/>

Blount married  Jackie Steigerwalt on December 27, 1958.<ref name="weigel">{{cite web |url=http://www.weigelfuneralhome.com/obituaries/James-Jim-Blount-2/#!/Obituary |title=Obituary for James 'Jim' Blount |website=Weigel Funeral Home |access-date=August 26, 2017}}</ref> They had two children, Brian and Lori.

Blount died in Hamilton, Ohio on August 22, 2017, at the age of 82.<ref name="weigel"/>

